usdIgmpMIB.name: usdIgmpMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

usdIgmpMIB.contactinfo: Unisphere Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdIgmpMIB.description: The IGMP MIB for Unisphere Networks, Inc. enterprise.

UsdIgmpProxyGroupState.name: UsdIgmpProxyGroupState
UsdIgmpProxyGroupState.description: IP multicast group state in respect to the host IGMP (IGMP proxy) behavior.

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceTable.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceTable
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceTable.description: The IGMP proxy interface table consists of interface on which the IGMP proxy is enabled.

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceIfIndex.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceIfIndex
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which the IGMP proxy is enabled.

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceAddress.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceAddress
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceAddress.description: The IP address of the interface for which the IGMP proxy is enabled.

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceMask.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceMask
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceMask.description: The IP subnet mask of the interface for which the IGMP proxy is enabled.

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceState.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceState
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceState.description: When the IGMP proxy interface has v1 router present timeout running, it is in IgmpIntfStateV1RtPresent state. Otherwise, it is in IgmpIntfStateNonV1RtPresent states. While it is in IgmpIntfStateV1RtPresent, it only sends out version 1 group membership report(s). While it is in IgmpIntfStateNonV1RtPresent state, it sends out version 2 group membership report(s).

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceStatus.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceStatus
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceStatus.description: The state of the IGMP proxy interface. This object follows the RowStatus behavior. The destruction of the the row deletes the IGMP proxy inteface.

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceVersion.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceVersion
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceVersion.description: The version of IGMP that this IGMP proxy interface is running.

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV1RoutePresentTimeo.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV1RoutePresentTimeout
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV1RoutePresentTimeo.description: The IGMP version 1 router present timeout is the time between IGMP proxy receives a version 1 query and the time it assumes that there is no more IGMP version 1 router IGMP running. While before the V1 router present timeout expires, the IGMP proxy only sends out version 1 group membership report. When it expires, it sends out version 2 group membership report.

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceUnsolicitedReportIn.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceUnsolicitedReportInterval
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceUnsolicitedReportIn.description: The unsolicited report interval specifies the time between the two initial group membership reports that the IGMP proxy sends.

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceTotalGroupCount.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceTotalGroupCount
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceTotalGroupCount.description: Total number of multicast groups for this upstream interface (interface running IGMP proxy).

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceWrongVersionCount.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceWrongVersionCount
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceWrongVersionCount.description: Total number of wrong version of IGMP packets received on this interface.

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV1QueryReceiveCount.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV1QueryReceiveCount
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV1QueryReceiveCount.description: Total number of version 1 IGMP queries received on this interface

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV2QueryReceiveCount.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV2QueryReceiveCount
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV2QueryReceiveCount.description: Total number of version 2 IGMP queries received on this interface.

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV1ReportReceiveCoun.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV1ReportReceiveCount
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV1ReportReceiveCoun.description: Total number of version 1 group membership reports received on this interface.

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV2ReportReceiveCoun.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV2ReportReceiveCount
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV2ReportReceiveCoun.description: Total number of version 2 group membership reports received on this interface.

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV1JoinReportCount.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV1JoinReportCount
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV1JoinReportCount.description: Total number of version 1 group membership reports sent on this interface.

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV2JoinReportCount.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV2JoinReportCount
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceV2JoinReportCount.description: Total number of version 2 group membership reports sent on this interface.

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceLeaveReportCount.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceLeaveReportCount
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceLeaveReportCount.description: Total number of group leave reports sent on this interface.

usdIgmpProxyCacheTable.name: usdIgmpProxyCacheTable
usdIgmpProxyCacheTable.description: The IP multicast group table. The table is a union of multicast member groups from all its downstream interfaces and for which the IGMP proxy send group membership report.

usdIgmpProxyIfIndex.name: usdIgmpProxyIfIndex
usdIgmpProxyIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which IGMP proxy is enabled.

usdIgmpProxyAddress.name: usdIgmpProxyAddress
usdIgmpProxyAddress.description: The IP multicast group address that the IGMP proxy sends group membership for.

usdIgmpProxyStatus.name: usdIgmpProxyStatus
usdIgmpProxyStatus.description: The state of this entry. When the IGMP proxy has a delay time running for this multicast group, the state of this enry is in the usdIgmpDelayingMember state. When the delay time expires, the IGMP proxy sends an unsolicited report and the state of this group enters usdIgmpDelayMember state.

usdIgmpCompliance.name: usdIgmpCompliance
usdIgmpCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities that implement the Unisphere IGMP MIB.

usdIgmpProxyInterfaceGroup.name: usdIgmpProxyInterfaceGroup
usdIgmpProxyInterfaceGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management of IGMP proxy interfaces in a Unisphere product.

usdIgmpProxyCacheGroup.name: usdIgmpProxyCacheGroup
usdIgmpProxyCacheGroup.description: An object providing management of IGMP proxy caches in a Unisphere product.
